                            <comment id="477106" author="pjones" created="Mon, 3 Nov 2025 19:08:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Charlie!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="477102" author="colmstea" created="Mon, 3 Nov 2025 19:01:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You can close this, I&apos;m still checking other distros/arches to ensure they&apos;re not booting with a duplicate IPV6 address. I can track any new issues with an ATM ticket and I&apos;ll link to this jira.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="476951" author="pjones" created="Sat, 1 Nov 2025 14:52:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is it ok to close this ticket out?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="476314" author="colmstea" created="Mon, 27 Oct 2025 22:15:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The script which creates our qcow2 snapshot images was not properly cleaning up the network config due to a syntax error. I corrected the error and rebuilt the el8.10 snapshots. The &apos;duplicate address&apos; error is no longer being thrown and the IPV6 address is getting set properly. I&apos;ll check other distros for this issue and correct them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
