&lt;pre&gt;[    2.940341] IPv6: eth0: IPv6 duplicate address fd33:3981:3213:f010:0:5254:8e:564e used by 52:54:00:83:41:fd detected!
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;some problem with the network configuration where same address is getting assigned to multiple hosts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="475773" author="adilger" created="Wed, 22 Oct 2025 20:02:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hornc&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hornc&quot;&gt;hornc&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=simmonsja&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;simmonsja&quot;&gt;simmonsja&lt;/a&gt;, is this a new regression in IPv6 testing?  I couldn&apos;t find any tickets that have this error message, but I &lt;em&gt;think&lt;/em&gt; it is different than &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18041&quot; title=&quot;struct obd_uuid is too small for MGC&amp;quot;NID&amp;quot; uuid with IPv6&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18041&quot;&gt;LU-18041&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
